tafsir[16]{c,v,t}:
  78,4,"The matter is not as they claim. These rejectors of the Qur’ān will soon know the evil outcome of their rejection."
  78,6,"Did I not make the earth spread out evenly for them so that it is fit for them to live on?"
  78,7,"And did I not put mountains on it like pegs to stop it from shaking?"
  78,8,"And O people! I created you of different types: some of you are males while others are females."
  78,11,"And I made the day a field for earning and finding provision."
  78,13,"And I made the sun an extremely bright and hot lamp."
  78,14,"And I sent some clouds for which the time has come to pour down with abundant rain."
  78,15,"So that through it I can extract different types of grains and crops."
  78,16,"And extract gardens that entwine with one another due to the closeness of the branches of their trees."
  78,19,"And the sky will open up; it will have gaps like open doors."
  78,20,"And the mountains will be made to move until they become like dispersed dust particles; becoming like a mirage."
  78,23,"Wherein they shall stay for endless ages and years."
  78,26,"As a requital in accordance to the disbelief and deviance they were on."
  78,28,"And they vehemently rejected My verses I revealed to My Messenger."
  78,29,"I recorded and counted each of their deeds; they are all written in their books of deeds."
  78,30,"O transgressors! So endure this everlasting punishment; I will not increase you except in punishment upon your punishment."